---
description: Every source file starts with a one-line English file-level comment
globs: '**/*.{ts,tsx,vue}'
alwaysApply: false
---

# File header

- The **first line** of every new or substantially edited source file MUST be a single-line `//` (TS/JS) or appropriate comment style for the file type summarizing purpose/responsibility.
- Style: concise, like `// Fixed-position final-FEN board preview on row hover via data-game-id, without prop-driven churn on the table body.`
- When creating a file, add this comment before imports and before the module body.
- Do not remove existing headers when editing unrelated code.
